Under the authority of the Public Health Surveillance and Planning Coordinator and the supervision of the Senior Analyst, the Data Analyst will contribute to the analysis and management of survey data, the production of reports, and the issuance of recommendations following the collection of data from health surveys in Nunavik. The analyst will contribute to the whole process of planning and implementing health surveys.
Your Responsibilities Will Include
 Collaborate in the design and planning of health surveys (including reviewing collection tools and methodology); Develop, validate and optimize data analysis tools; Analyze and interpret the data taking into account the realities of the field, with the support of a senior analyst; Validate the various survey processes, including the questionnaire, and data collection, through interviews and focus groups Assist in the development of dissemination strategies for survey results Collaborate in the development of various surveillance products; Issue recommendations following the analysis of survey data.
The Health Survey Data Analyst may also be called upon to work with other files related to the team.
Qualifications Requises
Undergraduate university degree in a relevant discipline such as geography, statistics, health sciences, international development, with a technical focus.
Master's degree considered an asset
However, a combination of training and relevant experience may be considered;
Experience in quantitative analysis and knowledge of data analysis software;
Experience in organizing focus groups with the objective of validating the various survey processes;
Experience in disseminating survey results;
Knowledge of the various provincial, federal and Inuit socio-sanitary databases;
Rigor and capacity for synthesis;
Good adaptation capacity;
Ability to maintain links with local, provincial and national partners;
Knowledge of the realities of Nunavik and Inuit culture, an asset;
Excellent knowledge of two of the three languages used in the region: Inuktitut, English or French; The ability to work in a team;
Knowledge of Voxco software, an asset;
Knowledge of the Office 365 suite.
Conditions et avantages
Two-year temporary full-time position (35 hours/week) with possibility of extension
Telework position
Salary according to standards established by the MSSS (27.08$ to 47.98$/hour)
